  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\n\r\nUpgrading Status from Release 1.8.0 on to latest nightly build develop 1.8.0 (20201111025927) brings an crash issue which happens when app is put on background.\r\nInstalling clean nightly develop build doesn't have such bug.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nCan proceed using Status after put on background if upgraded from release 1.8\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nApp crashes when put on background after upgrade from Release 1.8 to develop 1.8.0 (20201111025927)\r\n\r\n#### Notes\r\n\r\nNOTE: if I have enabled Notifications in Release 1.8 and then upgraded it's visible that notifications service restarts at this point (visible by pop-up at the top 'Notification service is started')\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Install Status from PlayStore (v1.8)\r\n- Create new user\r\n- _Optionally_ Enable notifications\r\n- Upgrade on to develop build (https://status-im-nightlies.ams3.digitaloceanspaces.com/StatusIm-201111-025900-ae3936-nightly-universal.apk)\r\n- Open Status and login to account\r\n- Put app on background\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status version: upgrade from 1.8 release onto develop 1.8.0 (20201111025927)\r\n- Operating System: Android 8, 9\r\n\r\n#### Logs\r\n\r\nFull logcat when opening Status and put on background till crash: \r\n[logcat_crash_when_backround.txt](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/files/5523878/crahs_backround222.txt)\r\n",
